Preposterous plot with holes you could drive a bus through...the main one being that it becomes clear very early on that the whole escape and evasion of Liam Neeson was unnecessary. The attempt to frame him was absolutely terrible and he would have been cleared in days and the evidence that proved who did do it would have been found quickly and easily by the police, no clever police work required.

Utterly lazy of the film makers and writers to come up with such a pointless mission for him. He ends up destroying property, assaulting police officers, killing people, and almost certainly injuring civilians to find out nothing that wouldn't have been discovered quickly anyway. Even his daughter wasn't actaully in danger until he was a threat to the bad guys...

Comment:
Watching this movie will give you a headache. The story is good but there are far too many jump cuts in every scene, especially the more action-y scenes. If you were to average all the cuts in the movie, apart from the credits, the camera will jump back and forth in perspectives every half second. Despite sitting through this once, saying "I did like the story..." I'm never watching it again. I had a headache less than half way through the movie.

If you want to watch this unnecessarily disorientating, short attention-span inducing movie, go ahead. It has some worth to it, but I deem it unwatchable due to bad editing. Blame the editor! Ha. Ha. Maybe just cut it up into 4 episodes to help reduce the risk of headaches due to excessive cuts.
Just an honest opinion..

SIMPLY AN EXCELLENT ACTION MOVIE with a moving story.

All the reviews I read were negative! Then I went to see this movie because Liam Neeson is such an amazing actor. And once again, it is a moving great movie only because of Liam Neeson especially is the main character.

It is an action movie and, as such, it is excellent. But Liam Nesson never fails to be extremely moving. You might even shed a few tears, as it is at times really moving. Liam Neeson is simply really great; without him, this movie would not be the same.

If you have a heart and enjoy action too, you will love Liam Neeson and this story. Highly recommended.

Title: TAKEN 3 | Official Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
I really wish they didn't kill of Famke Janssen. ¬†It always drives me nuts when characters are unceremoniously killed off, and in this case especially, consider a huge part of the last film was her being saved. ¬†It makes everything that came before feel fundamentally pointless in a way. ¬†

Now, I have no problem with characters being killed off if it's meaningful, but this looks like they didn't know what to base the story around, so they just said "Revenge! ¬†How about we kill off the wife?" ¬†And that's just a bit too lazy in my opinion, and invalidates the second film entirely. ¬†(And I know the second movie wasn't good, but still... ¬†why make it even worse by making it pointless in retrospect by killing off one of the leads?) ¬†Still, this looks to be a pretty awesome film despite that complaint, and it looks better than "Taken 2."
